cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.ET 

Reasoning: 

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the development of a linear logical framework to reason about the type system of a quantum lambda calculus. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the type system of a quantum programming language called Quipper. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of a practical version of Quipper called Proto-Quipper. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly mention any machine learning techniques or applications. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is also a less likely category as the paper focuses on the development of a specific programming language and its type system, rather than a broader discussion of emerging technologies.
